<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 81; Nasdaq Falls 15  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 81 points in today's
early going. Advancing and declining issues are evenly split on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 15 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is up two.
</P>
<P>
	   If the market follows recent form, we can expect to see what analysts say is
a rotation out of blue-chip stocks and into technology plays today.
</P>
<P>
	   That process left the Dow with a 230-point loss on Friday and its first
close below ten-thousand since last April.
</P>
<P>
	   As a result, the Dow is about 16 percent below the record high it set
January 14.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq, however, continues to flirt with new highs.
</P>
<P>
	   Overseas market averages have been uniformly lower today, with traders
saying they plan to watch Wall Street's early moves.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
