<DOCNO> APW20000228.0085 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-28 14:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Supreme Court Actions Summarized  </HEADLINE>
   By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   The Supreme Court took these actions Monday:
</P>
<P>
	   --Agreed to use a South Carolina dispute to decide, probably in 2001,
whether public hospitals can test pregnant patients for drug use and tell police
who tested positive.
</P>
<P>
	   --Refused to reinstate a $10 million libel award a bank executive and his
company won, and then lost, against ABC over a ``20/20'' news story he says made
him look like a crook. The justices rejected an appeal by Alan Levan, chairman
and chief executive of BFC Financial Corp.
</P>
<P>
	   --Turned away the appeal of a 78-year-old retired foundry supervisor in
Detroit who was ordered deported after he was found to have served as a guard at
two Nazi concentration camps during World War II.
</P>
<P>
	   --Rejected an appeal in which U S West, a major regional phone company,
sought permission to sell another firm's long-distance service to its local
customers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-28-00 1412 </TRAILER>
