<HEADLINE> Caine Won't Prepare Oscar Speech  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- To avoid bad luck, Michael Caine won't prepare an acceptance
speech for the Academy Awards.
</P>
<P>
	   "I see people go up there and get a piece of paper and I think, 'Jesus, you
must be confident!"' he joked to GMTV on Monday. "I have no speech really."
</P>
<P>
	   Caine, up for best supporting actor for "Cider House Rules," said he was
delighted to be nominated but considered it a tough category this year.
</P>
<P>
	   He has been nominated four times before, winning once for his supporting
role in the Woody Allen film "Hannah and Her Sisters."
</P>
<P>
	   Caine said he would take his wife, Shakira, and two daughters to the March
26 Oscar ceremony in Los Angeles.
</P>
