<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Monday, Feb. 28, 2000
</P>
<P>
	   Dow Ends Up 176.53; Nasdaq Slips
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrials advanced today as
bargain hunters grabbed shares at reduced prices following last
week's big selloff. Technology issues, which slumped from a bout of
profit-taking early today, bounced back in late trading. The Dow
rose 176.53 to close at 10,038.65, climbing above the 10,000-mark
that it fell below Friday. The Nasdaq composite index fell 8.62 to
4,581.88. In recent weeks, much of the stock market -- especially
blue-chip shares -- has been battered by fears that the Federal
Reserve will raise interest rates to reduce inflationary pressures.
But today, investors were bargain-hunting.
</P>
