Pittsburgh-based company a larger stake in the baby foods industry.
Terms of the merger were not disclosed. St. Louis-based Milnot's
largest subsidiary is Beech-Nut Nutrition Corp. Together, Heinz and
Beech-Nut make up about 24 percent of the U.S. prepared baby food
category. But it's still a a far cry from Gerber, the industry
leader with 73 percent of the market.
</P>
