<HEADLINE> 'Whole Nine Yards' Tops Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- "The Whole Nine Yards" held its ground at the box office
as the hitman comedy remained the top movie for the second straight weekend,
taking in $9.6 million.
</P>
<P>
	   "Snow Day" held strong at No. 2 with $8.3 million, while the holdup thriller
"Reindeer Games" debuted in third place with $8.1 million.
</P>
