<HEADLINE> Capitals 3, Islanders 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- Adam Oates scored his 300th career goal with 5:01
left Monday night, giving the Washington Capitals a 3-2 victory over the New
York Islanders.
</P>
<P>
	   Oates rushed down the right side on a 4-on-4 with Steve Konowalchuk. His
centering pass caromed off Aris Brimanis' skate past goalie Roberto Luongo to
give the Capitals their third win in four games.
</P>
<P>
	   Jeff Halpern and Ulf Dahlen also scored for Washington, which got 16 saves
from Olaf Kolzig. The Capitals trail Southeast Division-leading Florida by two
points with 19 games remaining.
</P>
<P>
	   Brimanis and Olli Jokinen scored for New York, which lost its fourth
straight and 10th in a row to the Capitals.
</P>
<P>
	   It was also the 13th consecutive time New York has failed to beat Washington
(0-12-1) -- including seven straight losses at Nassau Coliseum. The Islanders,
who got 34 saves from Luongo, have not beaten the Capitals since Dec. 7, 1996.
</P>
<P>
	   Both goalies stopped nine shots in a scoreless first period.
</P>
<P>
	   Brimanis picked up his first NHL goal at 1:46 of the second period -- during
New York's first power play -- on a 35-foot wrist shot from the left side that
got past Kolzig, who was screened.
</P>
<P>
	   Luongo made a brilliant stop about two minutes later, robbing Peter Bondra
by stretching his stick across the crease.
</P>
<P>
	   Washington tied it at 7:42 when Halpern, standing alone at the left crease,
flipped a rebound over Luongo.
</P>
<P>
	   Dahlen put Washington ahead at 11:53 on a one-timer from the low slot.
</P>
<P>
	   Jokinen made it 2-2 when his right circle wrist shot off a rush hit Kolzig's
outstretched right pad and shot up under the crossbar at 17:58.
</P>
