<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Stocks Higher at Midday  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- The Tokyo stock market's main index rebounded Tuesday morning
in reaction to a recovery on Wall Street. The dollar rose against the yen.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 225.27 points, or 1.14
percent, to 19,945.37 at the end of the morning session. On Monday, the average
closed down 97.79 points, or 0.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 109.78 yen in late morning, up 0.58 yen from late in Tokyo
and also above its late New York level of 109.37 yen.
</P>
<P>
	   On the stock market, the Nikkei index opened higher Tuesday as investors
were cheered by gains in New York, where the Dow Jones industrial average rose
176.53, or 1.79 percent, to 10,038.65 at Monday's close.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nikkei advanced on buying of major high technology issues, including
shares in Sony, Fujitsu, NEC and Canon.
</P>
<P>
	   Traders said the overall stock market was mixed as investors are poised to
take profits following recent gains.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section was down 0.21 points, insignificant in percentage terms, to 1,728.23.
The TOPIX closed up 3.94 points, or 0.23 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency dealings, traders said investors sold yen to buy dollars after
Tokyo on Tuesday said Japanese industrial production posted a
smaller-than-expected rise in January.
</P>
<P>
	   The Ministry of International Trade and Industry said Japan's industrial
output rose 0.9 percent last month from December. Economists surveyed by Dow
Jones Newswires earlier had projected on average industrial production would
increase 2.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 106.27 yen late Tuesday morning,
up from 105.37 yen late Monday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
	   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose to 1.8400
percent from Monday's finish of 1.8200 percent. Its price fell 0.17 point to
99.66.
</P>
</TEXT>
