<HEADLINE> Hartz Mountain Names New President  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SECAUCUS, N.J. (AP) -- The Hartz Mountain Corp. has appointed Robert Devine
president and chief operating officer, the company announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
	   The appointment is effective immediately, said Edward Stern, the current
president.
</P>
<P>
	   Devine, 47, joined Hartz in 1994.
</P>
<P>
	   Stern said Devine has more than 20 years experience in marketing, finance
and manufacturing in the pet supply industry.
</P>
<P>
	   Devine will report to Stern, who will replace his father, Leonard Stern, as
chief executive officer and chairman.
</P>
<P>
	   "I look forward to the opportunity to lead one of America's great companies
and brands," Devine said. "My goal will be to continue the direction established
by my predecessor ... with a strong focus on innovation through expanded
research and development and quality in manufacturing."
</P>
<P>
	   Hartz Mountain, founded in 1926, sells animal health and nutrition products
as well as treats and toys for dogs.
</P>
</TEXT>
